---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import { Sparkles, Terminal, Shield, Zap, Activity, Cpu } from 'lucide-react';
---

<DocsLayout title="What's New in v0.4.0">
  <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-zinc-500 mb-8">
    <a href="/docs" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Docs</a>
    <span>/</span>
    <span class="text-white">What's New</span>
  </nav>

  <div class="mb-12">
    <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-purple-500/10 border border-purple-500/20 text-purple-400 text-xs font-mono mb-4">
      <Sparkles size={14} />
      <span>RELEASE V0.4.0 - MARCH 2026</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4">The Security & Utility Update</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-zinc-400">
      Introducing proactive honeypot detection, streamlined token approvals, fast token conversions, and smart contract ABI tools.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3 mb-16">
    <div class="glass-card p-6 border-t-2 border-purple-500">
      <div class="text-purple-400 mb-4"><Shield size={24} /></div>
      <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-2">Honeypot Scanner</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">Detect malicious contracts instantly with <code>aura honeypot</code>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="glass-card p-6 border-t-2 border-green-500">
      <div class="text-green-400 mb-4"><Zap size={24} /></div>
      <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-2">Approvals Manager</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">Scan and revoke token allowances with <code>aura approve</code>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="glass-card p-6 border-t-2 border-blue-500">
      <div class="text-blue-400 mb-4"><Cpu size={24} /></div>
      <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-2">Token Conversion</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400">Easily swap tokens directly from your CLI with <code>aura convert</code>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">1. Proactive Scam Defense (aura honeypot)</h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-6">
      Protect your assets before you swap. <code>aura honeypot</code> simulates transactions to verify if a token can actually be sold, analyzing buy/sell taxes and detecting malicious contract behaviors.
    </p>
    <div class="terminal mb-6">
      <div class="p-4 font-mono text-sm">
        <span class="text-purple-400">❯</span> <span class="text-green-400">aura honeypot</span> <span class="text-yellow-400">0x...</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-zinc-400 ml-4">
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Simulates real buys and sells.
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Checks hidden taxes and blacklist capabilities.
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-green-500">✓</span> Simple "Safe" or "Honeypot" verdict.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">2. Token Approvals Manager (aura approve)</h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-6">
      Unlimited approvals to shady dApps are the number one cause of wallet drains. Use <code>aura approve</code> to quickly audit your wallet's allowances on any network and instantly revoke dangerous or unused approvals interactively.
    </p>
    <div class="terminal mb-6">
      <div class="p-4 font-mono text-sm space-y-1">
        <div><span class="text-purple-400">❯</span> <span class="text-green-400">aura approve</span> <span class="text-yellow-400">0xYourWallet... --revoke</span></div>
        <div class="text-yellow-400">⚠ Found 2 UNLIMITED approvals</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">3. Simple Token Conversion (aura convert)</h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-6">
      Quickly swap assets across supported dexes right from your terminal without opening a browser. Let Aura execute optimal paths securely and transparently.
    </p>
    <div class="terminal mb-6">
      <div class="p-4 font-mono text-sm">
        <span class="text-purple-400">❯</span> <span class="text-green-400">aura convert</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400 italic">
      Securely signed using your local encrypted vault.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">4. Developer Tooling (aura abi)</h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
      No more jumping to Etherscan to fetch ABIs. Retrieve and manage ABIs locally with a single command to streamline your scripting and interactions.
    </p>
    <div class="terminal mb-6">
      <div class="p-4 font-mono text-sm">
        <span class="text-purple-400">❯</span> <span class="text-green-400">aura abi</span> <span class="text-yellow-400">0x...</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="glass-card p-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">How to Update?</h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-6">
      Existing users can upgrade instantly via npm:
    </p>
    <div class="terminal mb-6">
      <div class="p-4 font-mono text-sm">
        <span class="text-purple-400">❯</span> <span class="text-green-400">npm install -g @felizz23/aura-os@latest</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex justify-center">
      <a href="/docs/commands" class="btn-primary text-sm py-2 px-8">
        Full Command Reference
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
